<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000024#     2#        626.1#">Va. Code Ann. § 24.2-626.1</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_24.2-626.1"/><heading><desig>§ 24.2-626.1.</desig><title>Acquisition and use of accessible voting devices</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><bodyText><p>The governing body of any county or city shall provide for the use of a voting or counting system in all elections that shall:</p></bodyText><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_1"/><heading><desig>1.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Provide for at least one voting system equipped for individuals with disabilities at each polling place, including nonvisual accessibility for the blind and visually impaired, in a manner that provides the same opportunity for access and participation (including privacy and independence) as for other voters; and</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_2"/><heading><desig>2.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Provide alternative language accessibility when required by § 203 of the Voting Rights Act of 1965 <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="52 USC 10503"><content><span normalizedCite="52 U.S.C. 10503">(52 U.S.C. § 10503).<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1828#123#000052#      10503#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation></p></bodyText></level></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedC